text.tspan: Lord, I confess my heart’s impure
Although my mind with Thine agrees:
Some parts within would still not yield
Remind me, Lord, of what love is,
The heavens, spread from sky to sky,
Its vast dimensions, broad and high,
The vault of heav’n has billows soft;
They tell Thy care for me;
Such gentle, kind and tender love
Towards one so harsh towards Thee.
For birds aloft and trees aground,
Thy loving care for me abounds
Love vast, yet thorough; strong, yet sweet,
I’ll love Thee, Lord, with all my heart
I fain would learn from Thee,
That with my heart, though weak, I too
